<p>Start with your 3 to 5 core topics. Break each into 10 to 20 subtopics. Prioritize by keyword difficulty and business relevance.</p>
<p>Read our full guide on how to <a href="/blog/create-topical-map-seo/">create a topical map</a> for the complete process.</p>
<p><strong>Why this step matters:</strong> Without a map, you publish 30 disconnected posts that compete with each other. Sites with clear topic authority gained 23% organic visibility after Google's December 2025 update. Structure beats volume every time.</p>
<p><strong>Pro tip:</strong> Use your AI tool to brainstorm subtopics for each cluster. Ask it to generate 20 related questions for your pillar keyword. Then validate each one with a keyword research tool.</p>
